    • Constructor Detail

      • Flight

        public Flight(java.lang.String startTime,
              java.lang.String endTime,
              int duration,
              int seatsAvailable,
              int seatsTaken,
              java.lang.String flightNum,
              double cost,
              int id)
        This is a helper function that create appropriate variables for flights and give each an id so the user can choose from the available flights in the FlightController class.
        Parameters:
        startTime - Is the start time for a flight.
        endTime - Is the end time for a flight.
        duration - Anticipated time the flight will takes off and arrive to the destination.
        seatsAvailable - The amount of seats available on a flight.
        seatsTaken - The seats that are taken on a particular flight.
        flightNum - The flight number for a flight.
        cost - The cost for a flight.
        id - The id associated with a flight so the user can choose a flight with the assigned information.
